==English==

===Etymology===
From Neo-Latin [[glagoliticus]] < Serbo-Croatian [[глаголица]]/[[glagolica]] < [[OCS]] [[глагол|глаголъ]] ("word").

===Adjective===
'''Glagolitic'''

#Referring to or written in the oldest known Slavonic alphabet, created by Saint [[Cyril]] around 862–863 AD. It was soon replaced by the [[Cyrillic]] alphabet.

